            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Isn't that what `g:clipboard` already kinda does? (except that the array of clipboards has to be maintained by the user rather than neovim)\r\n\r\n@glacambre, Thanks for the hint! I ended up using this in my config:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.g.clipboard = {\r\n  copy = {\r\n    [\"+\"] = \"xsel -i -b\",\r\n    [\"*\"] = \"xsel -i -p\",\r\n  },\r\n  paste = {\r\n    [\"+\"] = \"xsel -o -b 2>/dev/null\",\r\n    [\"*\"] = \"xsel -o -p 2>/dev/null\",\r\n  },\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
